title: Bikewatching: Analyzing Bike Traffic in Boston
description: This project visualizes bike traffic patterns in Boston using geospatial data from Bluebikes and city bike lane datasets. By integrating Mapbox, D3.js, and real-time filtering, we analyze station usage trends, traffic flow, and the impact of time on arrivals and departures. The project includes interactive features like a time slider, dynamic circle scaling, and a color-coded legend to distinguish traffic flow directions.

title: Recipe Rating Analysis Project
description: This project explores the relationship between recipe ratings and preparation time using data from Food.com. By analyzing thousands of user-submitted ratings and recipe details, we aim to discover whether prep time influences how recipes are rated.
